Uncovered: The War on Iraq;;69;;78;;NC;;Using a wealth of different sources, Robert Greenwald investigates the motives and pretexts of the administration of former President George W. Bush for going to war in Iraq after 9/11. Greenwald's film dissects the different catalysts leading to the war, from the media's treatment of the issue to the practice of "data mining." A panel of experts lend their voices to this examination, including CIA analysts, a former CIA director, previous ambassadors and a weapons inspector.;;War,Documentary,History,Drama;;Robert Greenwald;;2004;;Bob Baer,Milton Bearden,Jeff Bornstein,John Dean;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1135882-uncovered_the_war_on_iraq